		<table width="100%">
		<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Necromancer: Lvls 1-24</b></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><A href="mailto:LilD6464@aol.com">Drakmyer Shadowthief</a> | 
		            7/28/2000 2:13:28 PM</b></font></p>
		         <a href="guides.asp">
		         <font face="verdana" size="2">Return to guide listing.</font></a>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">Lvl 1-24 Outlined for Easy Reference<BR>
<BR>
Well first off, may I begin that race does not matter, it is all personal preference. Every class has their own advantages and disadvantages. So play something that suits your style of play, dont look at stats. That said, I must inform everyone that I am a Dark Elf Necromancer, so the strategies in this insert may not apply to you. <BR>
<BR>
Lvl 1-4 <BR>
What to Fight: Anything that cons white and maybe blue. What I did was hunted around the newbie log in Nek Forest and sat there when tired. There are other newbies there to help you if you get in trouble with more than one creature. <BR>
Strategy: If you buy the pet, which I did, just fight alongside it and use the life tap spell when low on health. And always be on the lookout for decaying skeletons, they give the ever sought after bonechips. <BR>
<BR>
Lvl 5-8 <BR>
What to Fight: I soloed skeletons that wandered around Nek Forest. Again, they give bonechips, which are a must have. If you wanna group, you can get a prtner and take the pyramid (full of skeletons and the occasional zombie) but it may be rough trying to break the spawn. Dont go after the snakes, they poison and it could be lethal. <BR>
Strategy: Experiment with your new dots. Darkness is always a good spell to cast first, slowing the enemy for an easier escape and does damage at the same time. Always check your pet's health if you let him solo a little, if he dies, you may have to run to the zone or guards for your life. Will still have to melee for your pet at this lvl. <BR>
<BR>
Lvl 9-12 <BR>
What to Fight: I went into the East Commons with plenty of bonechips (fighting all those skeletons has its advantages) and fought Giant Spiders, Giant Scarabs, and Lions. I also grouped to take orcs when soloing got boring. <BR>
Strategy: The ever-useful fear spell is now available. Now you can start to let your pet tank for you, but you must remember to fear when your pets health is low. You still will have to melee along with pet, so I advise you get a Giant Snake Fang. Darkness creaure, then send in pet, load up with rest of dots, and then when pets health is low, fear and melee it till the death. <BR>
<BR>
Lvl 13-16 <BR>
What to Fight: I left East Commons and headed to Oasis. The exp is great here but it is very crowded. Another good thing is that the crocs wont aggro on you and you dont need to worry about starting trains. Again, when soloing got boring (as it usually does), I grouped to take orcs in Oasis and Dervish Cutthroats in Northern Ro. Getting to lvl 16 will be a breeze. <BR>
Strategy: With your new Darkness and Heat Blood, you will be unstoppable. You will be able to solo yellow crocs with ease. Use Leach in combination with your hp to mana spell (the name eludes me for the moment) for some free mana. I had the best of times hunting in Oasis, I hope you enjoy the experience too! <BR>
<BR>
Lvl 17-20 <BR>
What to Fight: I packed my bags for the long journey to Lake Rathe. If you thought the crocs in Oasis was good exp, you havent seen anything yet! The Aviak Guards (very easy to solo at 18, may need help at 17), are great exp. It does get boring to solo for 4 straight lvls, so I often grouped in South Karana at the Aviak City. At lvl 20 with your new spells, you should easily be able to solo Arena, if its not taken already! <BR>
Strategy: Not much to say here but take the strategies you learned in Oasis to camp Aviaks. Dont forget about your new Heart Flutter, which will lower stats of yur opponent. <BR>
<BR>
Lvl 21-24 <BR>
What to Fight: I stayed at Arena spawn with Aviak Guards. It is very easy to kill them, almost no chance of dying, and they still give great exp. But soloing these things for 8 lvls straight can get sooo boring. You will want to group at Aviak City if you havent already or try another strategy from another guide if you are too bored. <BR>
Strategy: New Allure of Death drastically reduces downtime. Used with Leach it is better than clarity I heard. Not much more to say than keep your tactics from last few lvls (see how it can get a little boring?) <BR>
<BR>
I am currently lvl 24 and if you wish to contact me, my name is Drakmyer and I'm on the Brell server.
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
				<td>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</td></tr>
