				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Just wanted to add a few things, one ... It's Sent of Dusk that lowers stats, not heart flutter. Hear Flutter is your new Disease based DoT that does upto 144dmg.<BR>
<BR>
Tips about the Pact series .. Use it! Always .. Dark Pact (what you get at lvl8) doess EXACTLY what breeze does (lvl16 ENC +mana spell). Only one difference, is uses hp, breeze doesn't. <BR>
Comparisions:<BR>
Breeze - adds +2mana for ever tick.<BR>
Dark Pact - does +2mana and -4hp per tick (2:4).<BR>
I HIGHLY suggest you med when you do this, you will practily soo NO loss in hp.<BR>
<BR>
Next .. lvl 20: Clarity (ENC lvl29) vs Allure of Death (NEC lvl20)<BR>
Clarity - does +2mana upto +7mana per tick. Meaning, at lvl29, it will only be as good as breeze.<BR>
Allure - does a 4:8 convertion. This I would suggest to use leach with, for you will see a lost of hp. This is lot better than lower lvl ENC (lvl29-23) giving you clarity. <BR>
<BR>
lvl34 - you get Call of Bone, changed you into a skeleton and does a 8:11 conversion.<BR>
 And so on after there.<BR>
<BR>
Basically, us necros be the best +mana spells inthe game (they are all self onl) we just pay for it cause it uses out hp. But then again, we get the best leach and almost best self heals (life taps).<BR>
I'm a lvl18 Necro at the moment and I can tell ya, HP is NOT my main consern, it's all mana baby :)<BR>
<BR>
As you can see, I have done my research on these .. Get to know your spells, you might be supprised on how they compare the other class's os the same nature.<BR>
<BR>
Xield<BR>
